<br>
What removing this would do, is essentially remove any kinda usefullness in specing to 50 CS purely, cause ripper sucks.  It will also generalize the rogue class (i.e. you wont have melee specialists, or DW specialists, or CS specialists etc), cause everybody will have around 50 buffed spec at something.  This would be a very very very bad change (enough to require a global respec imo), cause it would remove a lot of the individualality from the game.   I for one, would lose about 50-70+ poitns of weaponskill, 45ish off my CS cap (future potential of losing a possible 99), A.K.A total gimpage.  This &quot;bug&quot; has been in since release, which was several months ago, and now there are a lot of 50's out there (not just assassins) who would be effected negativly by this.  Nobody has anything to lose from leaving this in, but if you remove it, then its like a global nerf.  Its just much much more advantageous to allow this type of super specialization than it is to generalize everybody into the same template category. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=2013.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=2013.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2013.topic&index=17><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=2013.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=2013.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org